This paper focuses on vision-based control for a robot, specifically a high-speed drone racing task. This suggests that it is likely to fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a deep optical flow (DOF) dynamics model, which is a combination of optical flow and robot dynamics, indicating that it may also fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of machine learning, specifically model predictive control (MPC), suggests that it may also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The goal of the algorithm is to maintain visibility of important features (gates) while navigating, indicating that it may also fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning and vision-based control suggests that it may also fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
